GoogleCloudCommerceConsumerProcurementV1.description: Represents an account that was established by the customer with a service provider. When consuming services on external service provider's systems, the service provider generally needs to create a linked-account on their system to track customers. The account resource represents this relationship. Products/Services that are hosted by external service providers generally require an account to be present before they can be purchased and used. The metadata that indicates whether an Account is required for a purchase, or what parameters are needed for creating an Account is configured by service providers.

name.description: Output only. The resource name of the account. Account names have the form `billingAccounts/{billing_account_id}/accounts/{account_id}`.

provider.description: Required. The identifier of the service provider that this account was created against. Provider has the format of `providers/{provider_id}`.

properties.description: Output only. Set of properties that the service provider supplied during account creation.

approvals.description: Output only. The approvals for this account. These approvals are used to track actions that are permitted or have been completed by a customer within the context of the provider. This might include a sign up flow or a provisioning step, for example, that the provider can admit to having happened.

updateTime.description: Output only. The last update timestamp.

The approval has been granted by the provider.
The approval has been rejected by the provider. A provider may choose to approve a previously rejected approval, so is it possible to transition to Account.Approval.State.APPROVED.

reason.description: An explanation for the state of the approval.

updateTime.description: The last update timestamp of the approval.

GoogleCloudCommerceConsumerProcurementV1.description: Represents a purchase made by a customer on Cloud Marketplace. Creating an order makes sure that both the Google backend systems as well as external service provider's systems (if needed) allow use of purchased products and ensures the appropriate billing events occur. An Order can be made against one Product with multiple add-ons (optional) or one Quote which might reference multiple products. Customers typically choose a price plan for each Product purchased when they create an order and can change their plan later, if the product allows.

name.description: Output only. The resource name of the order. Has the form `billingAccounts/{billing_account}/orders/{order}`.

displayName.description: Required. The user-specified name of the order. Must be unique within a billing account.

provider.description: Provider of the products being purchased. Provider has the format of `providers/{provider}`.

account.description: The resource name of the account that this order is based on. Required if the creation of any products in the order requires an account to be present.

orderState.description: Output only. The state of the order.
enumDescriptions: Sentinel value. Do not use.
The order is active.
The order is cancelled.

The order is being cancelled either by the user or by the system. The order stays in this state, if any product in the order allows use of the underlying resource until the end of the current billing cycle. Once the billing cycle completes, the resource will transition to OrderState.ORDER_STATE_CANCELLED state.

stateReason.description: Output only. An explanation for the order's state. Mainly used in the case of `OrderState.ORDER_STATE_CANCELLED` states to explain why the order is cancelled.

lineItems.description: Output only. The items being purchased.

cancelledLineItems.description: Output only. Line items that were cancelled.

updateTime.description: Output only. The last update timestamp.

etag.description: The weak etag of the order.

GoogleCloudCommerceConsumerProcurementV1.description: A single item within an order.

lineItemInfo.description: Output only. Current state and information of this item. It tells what, e.g. which offer, is currently effective.

pendingChange.description: Output only. A change made on the item which is pending and not yet effective. Absence of this field indicates the line item is not undergoing a change.

changeHistory.description: Output only. Changes made on the item that are not pending anymore which might be because they already took effect, were reverted by the customer, or were rejected by the partner. No more operations are allowed on these changes.

GoogleCloudCommerceConsumerProcurementV1.description: A change made on a line item.

changeId.description: Output only. Change ID. All changes made within one order update operation have the same change_id.

changeType.description: Required. Type of the change to make.
enumDescriptions: Sentinel value. Do not use.
The change is to create a new line item.
The change is to update an existing line item.
The change is to cancel an existing line item.
The change is to revert a cancellation.

oldLineItemInfo.description: Output only. Line item info before the change.

newLineItemInfo.description: Line item info after the change.

changeState.description: Output only. State of the change.
enumDescriptions: Sentinel value. Do not use.
Change is in this state when a change is initiated and waiting for partner approval.

Change is in this state after it's approved by the partner or auto-approved but before it takes effect. The change can be overwritten or cancelled depending on the new line item info property (pending Private Offer change cannot be cancelled and can only be overwritten by another Private Offer).
Change is in this state after it's been activated.
Change is in this state if it was rejected by the partner.
Change is in this state if it was abandoned by the user.
Change is in this state if it's currently being provisioned downstream. The change can't be overwritten or cancelled when it's in this state.

stateReason.description: Output only. Provider-supplied message explaining the LineItemChange's state. Mainly used to communicate progress and ETA for provisioning in the case of `PENDING_APPROVAL`, and to explain why the change request was denied or canceled in the case of `REJECTED` and `CANCELED` states.

changeStateReasonType.description: Output only. Predefined enum types for why this line item change is in current state. For example, a line item change's state could be `LINE_ITEM_CHANGE_STATE_COMPLETED` because of end-of-term expiration, immediate cancellation initiated by the user, or system-initiated cancellation.
enumDescriptions: Default value, indicating there's no predefined type for change state reason.
Change is in current state due to term expiration.
Change is in current state due to user-initiated cancellation.
Change is in current state due to system-initiated cancellation.

changeEffectiveTime.description: Output only. A time at which the change became or will become (in case of pending change) effective.

createTime.description: Output only. The time when change was initiated.

updateTime.description: Output only. The time when change was updated, e.g. approved/rejected by partners or cancelled by the user.

GoogleCloudCommerceConsumerProcurementV1.description: Entitlement represents the ability to use a product or services associated with a purchase within a Project. When the customer creates an Order, the system will create Entitlement resources under projects associated with the same billing account as the order, for all products/services procured in the order. Users can enable/disable Entitlements to allow/disallow using the product/service in a project. Next Id: 22

name.description: Output only. The resource Name of the Entitlement. Entitlement names have the form `projects/{project_id}/entitlements/{entitlement_id}`.

order.description: Output only. Order associated with this Entitlement.

provider.description: Output only. Provider associated with this Entitlement. In the format of `providers/{provider_id}`.

productExternalName.description: Output only. External name of the product this entitlement is created against.

flavorExternalName.description: Output only. External name of the flavor this entitlement is created against. This field is populated when entitlement has currently associated flavor, it is empty when entitlement is UNAVAILABLE (if order is pending activation or order is already cancelled).

state.description: Output only. The state of the entitlement.
enumDescriptions: Sentinel value. Do not use.
Indicates that the entitlement is unavailable and cannot be enabled.
Indicates that the entitlement is enabled. The procured item is now usable.
Indicates that the entitlement is disabled. The procured item is not usable.

stateReason.description: Output only. An explanation for the entitlement's state. Mainly used in the case of `EntitlementState.ENTITLEMENT_STATE_UNAVAILABLE` states to explain why the entitlement is unavailable.

services.description: Output only. Services associated with the entitlement.

updateTime.description: Output only. The last update timestamp.

pendingChange.description: Output only. A change which is pending and not yet effective.

changeHistory.description: Output only. Changes that are not pending anymore, e.g. it was effective at some point, or the change was reverted by the customer, or the change was rejected by partner. No more operations are allowed on these changes.

startTime.description: When the credit becomes effective. If empty then there's no lower bound of credit's effective timespan (i.e. the credit becomes effective at the time of its creation). For credit creation, this cannot be in the past.

endTime.description: When the credit expires. If empty then there's no upper bound of credit's effective timespan (i.e. the credit never expires).

GoogleTypeMoney.description: Represents an amount of money with its currency type.

currencyCode.description: The three-letter currency code defined in ISO 4217.

units.description: The whole units of the amount. For example if `currencyCode` is `"USD"`, then 1 unit is one US dollar.

nanos.description: Number of nano (10^-9) units of the amount. The value must be between -999,999,999 and +999,999,999 inclusive. If `units` is positive, `nanos` must be positive or zero. If `units` is zero, `nanos` can be positive, zero, or negative. If `units` is negative, `nanos` must be negative or zero. For example $-1.75 is represented as `units`=-1 and `nanos`=-750,000,000.

agreementDocument.description: Full name of the agreement document that was agreed to for this consent, ## in the format of one of: commerceoffercatalog.googleapis.com/billingAccounts/{billing_account}/offers/{offer_id}/agreements/{agreement_id}/documents/{document_id}

enumDescriptions: Unspecified value for the state. Sentinel value; do not use.

GoogleCloudCommerceConsumerProcurementV1.description: Request message to revoke a consent.
Request message for check consents.

agreement.description: Required. Agreement to be checked against. A valid format would be - commerceoffercatalog.googleapis.com/billingAccounts/{billing_account}/offers/{offer_id}/agreements/{agreement_id}

languageCode.description: The language code is used to find the agreement document if check consent doesn't pass. If this field is set, the method will attempt to locate the agreement document written in that language. If such document cannot be found, the request will fail. If this field is not set, the method will try two strategies in the following order: 1) reuse the language of document associated with the most recent consent, 2) use the document written in the default language, while default language is set by the agreement owner. If neither strategy works, the request will fail. Please follow BCP 47 (https://www.w3.org/International/articles/bcp47/) for the language string.
